OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 26 Mar to Sat 4 Apr
OL,6,FStill rather changeable at the start
OL,7,Fof this period, with further frontal
OL,8,Fsystems moving across the UK, bringing
OL,9,Fsome rain and stronger winds at times.
OL,10,FThrough late March, high pressure is
OL,11,Flikely to be located to the west or
OL,12,Fsouthwest of UK, with a predominantly
OL,13,Fnorthwesterly airstream in place.
OL,14,FFurther weather fronts are likely to
OL,15,Fround this high, bringing occasional
OL,16,Frain to the north and perhaps east of
OL,17,Fthe country, whereas areas further
OL,18,Fwest stand a better chance of being
OL,19,Fdry. In this setup, it may be rather
OL,20,Fcool for most, with some overnight
OL,21,Ffrost where skies are clear and winds
OL,22,Flight. Into early April and high
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fpressure may become rather more
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fdominant, with many areas seeing dry,
OL,25,Fsettled conditions.
